<H3> <TI>   Salinas Seeks Liberation of Ex-Governor </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1501225894 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2044 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1501225894 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 15 Jan (EFE) -- According to press 
reports, Mexican President Carlos Salinas de Gortari asked today 
Jorge Madrazo, president of the National Human Rights Committee 
(CNDH), to take steps to liberate former Chiapas Governor 
Absalon Castellanos. 
  In an unofficial version released by the press, Salinas 
asked 
the CNDH president to establish contacts with the Zapatista 
National Liberation Army (EZLN) to attain the liberation of the 
soldier and politician, who was kidnapped by guerrillas in the 
early days of the conflict. 
  According to the press, the government is trying to handle 
this affair discretely in order to ease the negotiation with the 
captors. 
  EZLN Representatives had stated that they would subject the 
former governor to a summary trial for repressing the indigenous 
peoples and peasants of Chiapas during his regime. Castellanos 
was kidnapped from his San Joaquin Ranch in Las Margaritas 
Municipality, Chiapas State. 
  The doctors of the Social Security Institute, who were set 
free in Guadalupe Tepeyac Municipality, have reported that 
General Castellanos was still alive and in a normal condition. 
  According to a journalistic version, the EZLN has informed 
his relatives that they will subject the former governor's fate 
to a vote, whereas another version has reported the total 
silence of his captors and that the general was in the town of 
Maravillas Trinidad. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

