<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidential Candidates Approve of Amnesty Decree </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1701003994 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2335 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1701003994 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 16 Jan (EFE) -- The presidential 
candidates of the Institutional Revolutionary Party (PRI), 
National Action Party (PAN), and the Party of the Democratic 
Revolution (PRD) have stated their approval of the amnesty 
decree announced today by President Carlos Salinas de Gortari. 
  PRI candidate Luis Donaldo Colosio termed as timely and 
welcome the initiative, which will settle the situation in 
southern Chiapas State, adding "everything done to attain peace 
in the region is welcome." 
  PAN candidate Diego Fernandez de Cevallos said everything 
that leads to the achievement of peace and justice must be 
supported by all Mexicans, adding that if the amnesty is the 
only option that guarantees peace, "I support the government's 
decision." 
  Fernandez de Cevallos said events in Chiapas do not endanger 
the conditions for holding elections this year; quite the 
contrary--they prove the people's clamor for a fair and 
democratic electoral process. 
  Cuauhtemoc Cardenas Solorzano, PRD candidate, said the 
proposed amnesty for the armed people in Chiapas represents a 
step toward creating conditions that allow a settlement and 
understanding on the conflict. 
  Cardenas--who termed as positive the fact that the 
government 
has decreed a ceasefire and is willing to decree an 
amnesty--stated his confidence solutions will soon be found to 
the state's problems. 
  The PRD candidate considered it urgently necessary to grant 
Indian representatives access to positions in which decisions 
are adopted to solve the conflict. 
  Cardenas demanded the replacement of acting Chiapas Governor 
Elmar Setzer with another who has the Indian communities' 
support and recognition. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

