<H3> <TI>   Menem Cuts Uruguay Visit Short; No Explanations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1701222994 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1955 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1701222994 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 17 Jan (NA) -- President Carlos Menem 
cut his visit to Uruguay short and this afternoon he returned to 
Buenos Aires from the city of Colonia de Sacramento, where he 
attended the fifth Mercosur [Common Market of the South] 
presidential summit. 
  Menem arrived at the military area of "Jorge Newbery" 
Metropolitan Airport at 1545 local time [1845 GMT] and after 
staying a few minutes in the VIP lounge, he left for the Olivos 
presidential resident aboard a helicopter. 
  The president made no statement to reporters at the airport, 
where some minutes earlier Economy Minister Domingo Cavallo also 
had arrived from Colonia. 

