<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   BCV Expels Banco Latino From Chamber of Compensation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1601151494 Caracas EL UNIVERSAL In Spanish 14 Jan 94 p 1-1 </F>
<F P=103> PA1601151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas EL UNIVERSAL In Spanish 14 Jan 94 p 1-1 </F>



<TEXT>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the Venezuelan Central Bank] </F>
  [Text] The Venezuelan Central Bank [BCV], as part of its 
duties as a clearinghouse bank, has excluded Banco Latino, C.A. 
from the clearinghouse system. 
  The decision was made when Banco Latino's debit balance 
could 
not be paid on 12 January at the Chamber of Compensation's close 
of business due to a shortage of funds in its BCV account. As a 
result, the procedures established in Article 12 of the Chamber 
of Compensation's regulations had to be enforced. 
  Consequently, Banco Latino will cease to participate in the 
Chamber of Compensation System. The BCV has notified the 
Superintendency of Banks, Fogade [Deposit Guarantee Fund], the 
finance minister, and the president of the National Banking 
Council of its decision so each of them can do their duty in 
accordance with the law. 
  This case will be handled by the competent institutions, 
which will apply the new banking legislation, so the normal 
functioning of the financial system should not be affected. The 
BCV hopes this situation will be resolved in the most 
constructive manner by the appropriate bodies to guarantee the 
enforcement of the savings, payments, and financial intervention 
systems. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

