<F P=100> INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Presidents Arrive for Mercosur Talks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1401155794 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1409 GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1401155794 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 14 Jan (NA) -- Uruguayan President 
Luis Alberto Lacalle and Paraguayan President Juan Carlos 
Wasmosy arrived here this morning to participate in a series of 
meetings with Argentine President Carlos Menem. 
  Lacalle and Wasmosy were met by Menem at the military sector 
of the Jorge Newbery Airport. They immediately departed for the 
South Coastal Avenue where they will participate in the ceremony 
of the opening of the bids for dredging a stretch of the Parana 
River, an undertaking within the framework of the so-called 
river highway that will join the port of Caceres in Bolivia with 
the port of Palmira in Uruguay. 
  The three chiefs of state will then have lunch at the Olivos 
residence where they will discuss matters pertaining to the 
Mercosur [Common Market of the South]. 

</TEXT>

