<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments Through 17 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1701222394 </F>
<F P=103> PA1701222394 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Peruvian economic developments monitored by Panama 
Bureau through 17 January; source follows in parentheses after 
item. 
  Guillermo Albareda, secretary of the Gold Committee of the 
National Mining Society (Sociedad Nacional de Mineria, SNM), has 
said that whereas Peru produced 18 tons of gold during 1992, it 
produced 28 tons during 1993. He added that 70 percent of the 
gold was obtained by new or expanded companies. Among the major 
investments he has cited were the Yanacocha Mine in Cajamarca 
Department, which the U.S. company Newmont Mining has been 
exploiting since last year, with an initial investment of $50 
million. He has also attributed the growth in this sector to 
expansion and modernization in the Retamas and La Poderosa 
Mines. (Madrid EFE in Spanish 2042 GMT 12 Jan 94) 

</TEXT>

