<H3> <TI>   Council Requests Explanation on Presence of U.S. Troops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1801212394 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1801212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Interview with Colombian Council of State President Amado </F>
Gutierrez by reporter J.J. Pinilla at the Council of State 
offices in Santa Fe de Bogota on 18 January; from the "National" 
newscast -- live or recorded] 
  [Text] [Pinilla] Your attention, please. The Council of 
State has just asked the government for an explanation regarding 
the overflight of foreign aircraft and the presence of U.S. 
troops in our country. Mr. Amado Gutierrez, president of the 
Council of State, what have you requested of the president? 
  [Gutierrez] The petition, which was approved unanimously 
during a plenary Council meeting, requests the president to 
inform us about the legal conditions under which he granted 
authorization for several military aircraft to overfly the city 
of Barranquilla and for foreign troops to remain in several 
areas of the country. 
  [Pinilla] Why has the Council of State made such a request? 
  [Gutierrez] The Council of State made the request because 
the 
Constitution expressly states that while the Senate is in 
recess, the movement of foreign troops may only be authorized by 
the president, with prior approval by the Council of State. 
  [Pinilla] Thank you for your kindness, Mr. Amado Gutierrez, 
new president of the Council of State. 

