<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Developments Through 18 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1801131794 </F>
<F P=103> PA1801131794 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Honduran economic developments monitored through 18 
January. Source is cited in parentheses following each item. 
  Official sources said Honduran banana production will drop 
by 
5 million cases -- 18 kg each -- in 1994. According to official 
estimates, Honduras will produce 35 million cases in 1994, 
compared to 40 million produced in 1993. The reasons given for 
this were floods at the end of 1993 and EC protectionist 
measures. (Panama City ACAN in Spanish 1637 GMT 12 Jan) 
  Honduran international reserves dropped approximately $100 
million during the past few months, to the point that there are 
only $131 million in the Central Bank vaults. This is only 
enough foreign exchange to back imports for one month, official 
sources reported on 12 January. (Panama City ACAN in Spanish 
1632 GMT 12 Jan 94) 
  Finance Ministry official William Chong reported that the 
government failed to collect 1 billion lempiras in taxes, 
including sales and income taxes. Chong admitted that this is 
due in part to corruption and irregularities in the Customs 
Department. (Tegucigalpa EL PERIODICO DE HONDURAS in Spanish 13 
Jan 94 p 3) 

</TEXT>

