<F P=103> PA1901001594 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua BARRICADA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guillermo Potoy and Alfredo Cesar, president and 
secretary of the Social Democratic Party [PSD], respectively, 
have decided to expel, without prior consultation, all PSD 
militants holding government posts as well as PSD deputies who 
have decided to again take up their parliamentary posts. 
  Potoy and Cesar adopted this decision because this past 
Sunday, the PSD National Executive Committee issued a document 
calling for the election of new party authorities and backing 
the reforms to the Constitution. The expelled PSD members will 
give a news conference today. 

