<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   PDC President Accuses Former Comptroller of Favoring IFIS </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1901023194 Panama City Telemetro Television Network in 
Spanish 1730 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1901023194 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City Telemetro Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Telemetro Reports" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Christian Democratic Party [PDC] President Raul Ossa 
accused Ruben Dario Carles, former comptroller general and 
current presidential candidate, of surreptitiously paying off 
the IFIS [International Financial Institutions] while forfeiting 
the country's health, education, and economic stability. 
  [Begin recording] Our position has been quite clear. It is a 
fact that Mr. Carles chose to pay off the IFIS, even to the 
point of breaking the law. I have the letter he signed whereby 
he surreptitiously paid off the IFIS behind the back of the 
National Assembly Budget Commission. In doing this, he denied 
equipment to schools, the 13th month bonus to public workers, 
and medication to hospitals. He did all this while at the same 
time he paid off the IFIS. 
  In this respect, we believe this is not the type of policy 
which will be healthy for Panama. We believe Panama must honor 
its commitments to the IFIS. At the same time, however, we must 
honor the country's social debt, create more employment, provide 
more equipment for schools, more education for the people, 
medication to hospitals, and raise the retirement age. Carles 
does not intend to do any of this. He represents the denial of 
all of this. 

</TEXT>

