Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tandil, 17 Jan (NA) -- Juan Carlos Pugliese, a 
former Chamber of Deputies president, died today at 0900 in 
Tandil, his home town, where he lived since giving up public 
functions. 
  Pugliese was admitted to a local hospital by mid-week last 
week. 
  He was the president of the Chamber of Deputies from the 
reestablishment of democracy in 1983 to 1989 when he left to 
become economy minister during the final stretch of the Raul 
Alfonsin administration. 

