<F P=100> Uruguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Roundup of Economic Reports Through 13 Jan </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1301180094 </F>
<F P=103> PY1301180094 </F>
<F P=104></F>



<TEXT>
Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Uruguay monitored through 13 
January. Source is cited in parentheses following each item. 
  On 4 January, the Central Bank reported that the state 
registered a 357.2 million-peso deficit in the January-October 
1993 period. This was the result of the public sector's 
nonfinancial surplus of 73.8 million pesos and a 431 
million-peso deficit in the "parafiscal" sector. (Montevideo LA 
MANANA in Spanish 5 Jan 94 p 43) 
  The Central Bank's net international reserves increased 
$213.3 million in 1993; total reserves now amount to $1.1603 
billion, 22.5 percent more than in 1992. (Montevideo EL 
OBSERVADOR ECONOMICO in Spanish 6 Jan 94 p 9) 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

