<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chile Approves Special Line of Credit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1501013594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1501013594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Enrique Correa Rios, Chilean minister secretary 
general of government, today in Santiago, Chile, announced that 
a special line of credit for Cuba was approved today by the 
National Bank of Chile. The line of credit, in the amount of 17 
million German marks, approximately $10 million, will be used to 
purchase food. Correa said he believes this operation will 
benefit Chilean producers. Correa also stressed President 
Patricio Aylwin's participation in the approval of the credit 
given Cuba. 

</TEXT>

