<F P=102>  FL1801190194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1801190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina arrived in 
Zambia as part of a tour of Africa. The foreign minister has 
already visited Ghana, Angola, and Zimbabwe. Robaina traveled to 
Lusaka from Harare, where he visited for three days and met with 
Zimbabwean authorities. During his stay in Zambia, Robaina plans 
to meet with Zambian President Frederick Chiluba and other 
government authorities. The foreign minister also plans to visit 
Windhoek, Namibia, where he will meet with President Sam Nujoma. 
Namibia is scheduled to be the last stop of his first tour of 
Africa, which will end on Friday. 

