<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Electoral Tribunal Annuls Campaign Spending Resolution </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1901043694 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1901043694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Federal Electoral Tribunal has unanimously 
annulled the resolution approved by the General Council of the 
Federal Electoral Institute [IFE] on 23 December 1993. This 
resolution approved the procedure to determine the ceiling for 
presidential campaign spending. The IFE General Council had 
appointed three of its magistrates to establish the amount that 
would constitute the ceiling for presidential campaign spending. 
  The Federal Electoral Tribunal, however, decided that this 
procedure transfers the IFE General Council's decisionmaking 
power to the magistrates. Therefore, the Federal Electoral 
Tribunal, as explained by its president Jose Luis de la Peza, 
decided that the IFE General Council should issue a new 
resolution before 31 January. 
  [Begin de la Peza recording, in progress] ...by which it can 
determine the ceiling for the amount of money parties can spend 
on their campaigns for the presidential elections. [end 
recording] 
  In turn, the Federal Electoral Tribunal issued a resolution 
that took into account a suit filed against the IFE by the Party 
of the Democratic Revolution. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-51416 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat012_c_94005" </HT>


