<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Issues Bulletin No. 20 </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1801133494 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0435 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1801133494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Bulletin No. 20 issued by the Mexican National Defense </F>
Secretariat on the situation in Chiapas; place and date not 
given; from the "24 Hours" newscast] 
  [Text] Military personnel continue to provide security to 
the towns of San Cristobal de las Casas, Rancho Nuevo, Oxchuc, 
Altamirano, Ocosingo, Las Margaritas, Comitan, and Escopetazo in 
case of possible new attacks and in response to the civilian 
population's demand for the presence of troops. 
  Yesterday, residents in Oxchuc turned in to the authorities 
16 lawbreakers who participated in various vandalistic actions 
since 1 January. Social work continues through the distribution 
of food, blankets, medicines, and potable water. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
