<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Salinas Postpones Trip To Spain Due to Events </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1801172494 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1500 
GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1801172494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Panorama" newscast] </F>
  [Text] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari has postponed 
for an indefinite period his state visit to Spain due to the 
conflict in Chiapas State. The presidential trip was scheduled 
for the end of the month and was in response to the visit that 
King Juan Carlos paid to Mexico in January 1990. Spanish 
Government spokesmen indicated that the governments of the two 
countries are going to decide on a new date for the visit. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

