<H3> <TI>   Chiapas Provisional Governor Resigns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1801223794 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2149 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1801223794 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 18 Jan (EFE) -- Chiapas Provisional 
Governor Elmar Setzer presented his resignation to the state 
congress today. A Chiapas government source reported the 
congress has appointed Javier Lopez Moreno to replace him. 
  Setzer was appointed provisional governor in January 1993 
when Governor-elect Patrocinio Gonzalez was designated 
government secretary. 
  Lopez Moreno is the second provisional governor in Chiapas 
and takes Setzer's place as a result of the armed conflict in 
the region. 

</TEXT>

