<H3> <TI>   Army Reportedly Holds Chiapas Highland Communities </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1901030994 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0044 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1901030994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Bulletin No. 21 issued by the Mexican National Defense </F>
Secretariat on the situation in Chiapas on 18 January; place not 
given; from the "Vector 21" newscast] 
  [Text] In the Chiapas highlands, the Mexican Army continues 
to control San Cristobal de las Casas, Rancho Nuevo, Ocosingo, 
Altamirano, Las Margaritas, Comitan, and Oxchuc. The Army 
simultaneously does social work for these communities. 
  Residents of Las Islas, San Juan Tenampa, Santa Rita, common 
lands Eden and La Revancha, and delegates of the cattlemen's 
unions in Altamirano, Las Margaritas, Ocosingo, Comitan, and San 
Cristobal, have been reporting looting and cattle rustling by 
armed groups. 

</TEXT>

