<F P=100> INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Menem `Feared an Attack,' Left Uruguay </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1801181194 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 1500 GMT 18 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1801181194 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Itamar Franco this morning concluded his 
visit to Uruguay where he met with the other presidents of the 
Mercosur [Common Market of the South]. He left Montevideo at 
0900 and should be arriving in Brasilia at 1400. 
  Argentine President Carlos Menem also cut short his visit, 
leaving for Buenos Aires yesterday afternoon. He feared an 
attack and left under an unprecedented security blanket at a 
meeting of South America presidents. 

</TEXT>

