<H3> <TI>   M-19 Members Seize Church, Protest U.S. Troops' Presence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1201194994 Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 in Spanish 1730 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1201194994 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Inravision Television Cadena 
1 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Protests over the presence of U.S. troops at Malaga 
Bay continue. Today, several members of the M-19 [19 April 
Movement] reacted by seizing the cathedral in Ibague, the 
capital of Tolima Department. 
  Approximately, 20 M-19 members are inside the Ibague 
cathedral right now protesting the presence of U.S. troops in 
Colombia and the incidents with the Venezuelan National Guard. 
They announced the action at 0700 this morning when they began a 
hunger strike for the dignity of Colombia. 
  [Begin recording] [M-19 member Carlos Herazo] We want the 
president to explain to the country the agreement that the 
Colombian Government signed with the U.S. Government for these 
engineering maneuvers. 
  [Unidentified Reporter] What do you want? 
  [Herazo] We also want to criticize the Venezuelan Armed 
Forces' constant violations of our sovereignty. [end recording] 
  The protest by this group of Colombians here at the Ibague 
cathedral will last until tomorrow. 

</TEXT>

