<H3> <TI>   Bilateral Army Intelligence Meeting With Ecuador Announced </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1301035394 Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1652 GMT 10 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1301035394 </F>
<F P=104>  Hamburg DPA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 10 January (DPA) -- Colombian 
Government sources announced that a bilateral meeting between 
the Colombian and Ecuadoran Army intelligence directors started 
today in Santa Fe de Bogota. 
  During the meeting attempts will be made to find solutions 
to 
the public order problems that have occurred during the past 
weeks in the border region. These problems include the death of 
several Ecuadoran soldiers, which are believed to have been 
caused by the Simon Bolivar National Guerrilla Coordinating 
Board [CNGSB]. 
  Colombian Army Commander General Hernan Jose Guzman pointed 
out that during this meeting, which will be held behind closed 
doors, they will attempt to establish the accuracy of reports 
circulating in Colombia. These reports are related to Ecuadoran 
Army units arresting several Colombian peasants on Colombian 
territory and accusing them of being guerrilla members. 
  Likewise, the meeting is intended to "formulate plans 
against 
guerrilla and criminal activities in the border region between 
both countries," Gen. Guzman emphasized. The officer also 
pointed out that the meeting constitutes part of the agreements 
signed several weeks ago by both countries' defense ministers. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

