<H3> <TI>   Congratulates Eastern Army Units </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1601214094 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 2030 GMT 
16 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1601214094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Army General Raul Castro, second secretary of the 
Communist Party of Cuba and minister of the Revolutionary Armed 
Forces [FAR], has congratulated the Eastern Army for its 
accomplishments in 1993, when it upheld the status of the best 
command of the FAR. This was stated during the ceremony marking 
the beginning of the Eastern Army 1994 defense training year 
held at military unit No. 2034 in Las Tunas Province. This was 
due to the fact that this unit and its members performed in an 
outstanding manner in the province and earned the title of best 
for 1993. Division General Ramon Espinoza Martin, member of the 
Central Committee and chief of the Eastern Army, stated that 
this command, in addition to staying at the national vanguard in 
defense tasks, attained first place in the Eighth Science and 
Technology Forum. 

</TEXT>

