<H3> <TI>   More on Raul Castro Remarks to Reporters </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1501022694 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1501022694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As announced, we now feature the statement Army 
General Raul Castro made to reporters following the ceremony 
marking the beginning of the Central Army defense training year 
in Cienfuegos. 
  [Begin recording] Despite the special situation the country 
has been enduring for several years and which you know about, in 
the last three years -- to speak in concrete terms -- the 
Revolutionary Armed Forces, the Interior Ministry, and the 
entire gigantic force of militiamen, [words indistinct] the 
great army of the people which will be the ones conducting the 
doctrine of the war of the entire people are aware....[changes 
thought] Despite this, I repeat, everything we do despite the 
situation, all the sacrifices, and our limited resources, we 
continue to develop -- from the people's tunnels to the medium 
and large tunnels, which are part of the preparation of the 
theater of military operations, part of the entire gigantic 
effort by our people. All this has grown despite this situation, 
and there is one single goal: To prepare for war precisely in 
order to avoid war, which is our dearest hope. 
  Once we said in a meeting that the most beautiful battle or 
the greatest victory our people can attain is precisely avoiding 
war, which for us -- we have said this before -- is the same as 
to have won it. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

