<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   U.S. Broadcasters Association Demands TV Marti Closure </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1501011294 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 2320 GMT 
14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1501011294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The U.S. National Association of Broadcasters has 
demanded that TV Marti, the anti-Cuban television station, be 
closed. The association has described the station as 
inefficient and illegal. In statements to a special U.S. 
Congressional body, created to study the future of TV Marti and 
Radio Marti, (William Haratuntam), adviser to the National 
Association of Broadcasters, said that TV Marti violates the 
international agreements that limit the use of radio and 
television signals for domestic use only. The so-called TV 
Marti and Radio Marti have been on the air since May 1985 and 
March 1990, respectively. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

