<H3> <TI>   Meets Zimbabwean Acting President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1701191394 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1800 
GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1701191394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by PRENSA LATINA correspondent Eduardo Rodriguez </F>
from Harare] 
  [Text] Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina delivered a message 
from President Fidel Castro to Zimbabwean Acting President Simon 
Muzenda. Muzenda and Robaina held a short meeting at the 
Zimbabwean Executive Offices in Harare. 
  With this meeting, Robaina began the third and last day of 
his official visit to Harare. Robaina arrived in Harare on 
Saturday from Angola. This visit is part of a two-week tour of 
the African continent. The head of Cuban diplomacy will travel 
to Lusaka, Zambia tomorrow and from there to Namibia, the last 
leg of his tour, which also included Ghana and Angola. 
  Foreign Minister Robaina also met today with Zimbabwean 
Foreign Minister Nathan Shamuyarira. Shamuyarira described 
relations between Cuba and his country as excellent and 
expressed his hopes that bilateral exchange will be 
strengthened. The Zimbabwean foreign minister recalled that Cuba 
had done much for Africa, and that now the African countries 
must offer their support to a country facing difficult times. 
The Zimbabwean foreign minister encouraged an increase in 
contacts between the ruling ZANU-PF [Zimbabwe African National 
Union-Patriotic Front] and the Communist Party of Cuba and 
expanded cooperation and commercial exchange in other areas. 

</TEXT>

