<H3> <TI>   Jamaican, Guyanese Trade Ministers Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1501184194 Bridgetown CANA in English 1630 GMT 15 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> FL1501184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Bridgetown CANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Kingston, Jamaica, 15 Jan, CANA -- Jamaica and 
Guyana are exploring ways to strengthen cooperation between the 
two countries in trade investment promotion. 
  The state news agency Jampress said the effort, which will 
include joint projects between the two nations, was the focus of 
discussions between Jamaica's foreign affairs and foreign trade 
minister, Dr. Paul Robertson and Guyana's trade, investment, and 
tourism minister, Michael Shree Chan, this week. 
  Robertson pledged Jamaica's support for Guyana's efforts to 
develop trade and investment promotion mechanisms and to 
cooperate in other areas of natural interest in the economic 
sphere. 
  The two ministers discussed the long-standing relations 
between their two nations and economic measures being undertaken 
to liberalise their economics and gear them to meet the 
challenges of the new global economy. 

</TEXT>

