<H3> <TI>   Malval Ministers Immobilize State Operations </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1401173994 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 2000 
GMT 13 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1401173994 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The ad interim Prime Minister Robert Malval is 
unable to assemble his ministers. According to an informed 
source, the government is reportedly immobilized due to Mr. 
Malval's inability to assemble a majority of the government's 
members. At least six members of the team that resigned 15 
December have reportedly refused to participate in the ministers 
council convened by Robert Malval. 
  This situation involves the ministers who dissociated 
themselves from Mr. Malval following the leak of a letter 
addressed to the president of the Republic, Jean-Bertrand 
Aristide. The government is reportedly unable therefore to take 
measures to execute decisions related to certain day-to-day 
matters of state. 

</TEXT>

