<H3> <TI>   Group Threatens Actions if Demands Are Not Met </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1501010794 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1130 
GMT 14 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1501010794 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Haitian citizens met in a national committee for the 
resolution of the crisis and plan to go into the streets on 21 
January in order to require the forming of a government of 
national agreement and the lifting of the embargo. The 
committee threatens to invest an executive [words indistinct] if 
its demands are not taken into account. After 28 months of 
murderous crisis, says the committee, the solution is the 
streets, asserting that it is possible to have the unfair 
punishment inflicted by the international community on the 
Haitian people stopped through nonviolence. According to the 
committee, it is not good to witness the collapse of our social 
and cultural life, of our national economy, and of the actual 
and daily sacrifice of many thousands of Haitians. The 
committee hopes to mobilize all vital forces of the nation 
throughout the nine geographic departments of the country. 

</TEXT>

