<H3> <TI>   Eustace John Sworn in as Nevis Deputy Governor General </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL1701181094 Bridgetown CANA in English 1510 GMT 17 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> FL1701181094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bridgetown CANA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Basseterre, St. Kitts, 17 Jan, CANA -- A career 
civil servant, Eustace John, has been sworn as the new deputy 
governor general of Nevis. He succeeds the late Weston Parris, 
M.B.E. who died in office almost two years ago. 
  John was sworn in by resident Puisne judge, Velma Hylton, in 
the presence of prime minister Dr. Kennedy Simmonds, Nevis 
Premier Vance Amory, family members, friends, and well wishers. 
  The new deputy governor general is a former director of 
audit. He was also general manager of the state-owned ZIZ Radio 
and Television. John holds a certificate in Mass Communications 
from the Caribbean Institute of Mass Communications (Carimac) at 
the University of the West Indies (UWI) Mona Campus. 

</TEXT>

