<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Issues Bulletin Announcing Cease-Fire </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1201205194 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
2000 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1201205194 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Bulletin issued by the National Defense Secretariat in </F>
Mexico City on 12 January; from the "24 Hours" newscast -- read 
by announcer] 
  [Text] In compliance with an order from the president of 
the Republic and supreme armed forces commander, the Mexican 
Army and Air Force will act as follows: 
  They will not open fire on armed groups unless they attack 
the Army or Air Force, directly endanger the civilian 
population, or try to return to towns or positions they 
initially occupied. Specifically, the Air Force will suspend its 
fire, except in cases of aggression against Army personnel who 
require its support in unpopulated areas. 
  They will continue to protect towns that requested their 
help 
to prevent possible attacks. They will not permit any movement 
by these armed people to areas outside the region. They will 
maintain the free mobilization of their personnel and equipment, 
including ground patrol and air reconnaissance. They will 
redouble their contribution to the government effort to 
distribute food, medicines, and other items which are basic to 
the affected population. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

