<F P=101> Chiapas Crisis </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Reports Recapture of Chiapas Towns </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1201134494 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1301 GMT 12 Jan 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1201134494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Mexico City, 12 Jan (NOTIMEX) -- The National 
Defense Secretariat [Sedena] reported today that the most 
important towns in Chiapas initially occupied by the armed 
groups have been recovered. Thus the first objective of the 
military operation "has been achieved." 
  In its Communique No. 14, Sedena states that by achieving 
this first objective, the Mexican Army has taken territorial 
control of the area in general and that civilian authorities 
have already begun exercising their responsibilities. 
  The text of the Sedena communique follows: 
  "In accordance with the planned operations as drafted by the 
7th Military Region Command based in Tuxtla Gutierrez, Chiapas, 
we have achieved the first objective of the operation, which is 
the recovery of the most important towns taken over by the 
transgressors, with the exception of Guadalupe Tepeyac, which 
should take place as soon as a large number of installations 
destroyed by the assailants on the various roads are repaired. 
  "In achieving this first objective, the Mexican Army has 
recovered territorial control of the area in general. Civilian 
authorities are exercising their responsibilities in all 
municipal capitals taken over by the assailants. No area of 
significance in the region is being occupied by these armed 
people, even though some isolated groups may still be operating." 

</TEXT>

