<H3> <TI>   Defense Secretariat Explains Aircraft Missions in Chiapas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1201131694 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1200 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1201131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1200 GMT 12 Jan 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "At Daybreak" newscast] </F>
  [Text] On the night of 11 January, the National Defense 
Secretariat issued Press Communique No. 13, explaining the 
missions conducted by military aircraft in the Chiapas conflict. 
The Defense Secretariat reports that up to now, operations by 
Air Force airplanes and helicopters in direct support of the 
ground forces are no closer than 5 km to the towns, so 
townspeople have not been harmed in any way. The communique 
adds that the aircraft have been used to transport troops and 
supplies. They have also been transporting food, medicine, 
clothing, and other articles to be distributed among residents 
of towns where military personnel are conducting activities to 
help civilians. 

</TEXT>

