<H3> <TI>   Rebel Attacks Expected in `Next 24 Hours' </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1901200694 Mexico City Radio Acir Network in Spanish 1927 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA1901200694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio Acir Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Bulletin No. 22 issued by the Mexican National Defense </F>
Secretariat on the situation in Chiapas; place and date not 
given; from the "Vector 21" newscast] 
  [Text] The National Defense Secretariat reports it has 
knowledge that in the next 24 hours rebel groups plan to stage 
armed attacks against the communities of Yajalon, Sabanillas, 
and Venustiano Carranza. 
  Meanwhile, reports have been received from residents of the 
region that on 17 January approximately 20 armed individuals, 
who had their faces covered, stole numerous head of cattle from 
a ranch located between the communities of Copainala and 
Coapilla. Up until now, soldiers continue guarding the 
communities mentioned in previous communiques and continue to 
carry out social work in these communities. 

</TEXT>

