<H3> <TI>   Peace Commissioner Appeals for Peace, Reconciliation </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2001030494 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 0043 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2001030494 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vector 21" newscast] </F>
  [Text] At about noon today, Manuel Camacho Solis, special 
commissioner for peace and reconciliation in Chiapas, delivered 
a very brief message over the local radio. The message read as 
follows: 
  This is Manuel Camacho Solis and I am the commissioner for 
peace. President Carlos Salinas de Gortari has approved an 
amnesty law. We are now waiting for its approval by the National 
Congress. This law will help us attain peace. 
  The message adds: It is necessary to beg the Indians'and the 
communities' forgiveness for all the suffering they have 
endured. Now is the time to stop bothering one another. Now is 
the time to look after our families. Let everyone work in his 
own home and let everyone have tranquility in his community. 
  The message goes on to say: There is a new governor. He is 
going to send his representatives to help you and your 
communities. Now is the time to work again in the [word 
indistinct], to take care of your families, and improve Chiapas. 
Chiapas is everything. Let us all make an effort to build peace 
in Chiapas. 

</TEXT>

