<H3> <TI>   Rebels Say Conditions for Dialogue Unfulfilled </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2101133094 Paris AFP in Spanish 0842 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2101133094 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] San Cristobal de las Casas, Mexico (AFP) -- The 
"prior conditions" to begin a dialogue with the government have 
not been fulfilled "in their entirety," because the Army 
"continues to violate the cease-fire," the Mexican guerrillas 
stated in two communiques published in the local newspaper 
TIEMPO on Friday. 
  The documents, which AFP received tonight in advance, are 
addressed to Peace Commissioner Manuel Camacho and Samuel Ruiz, 
bishop of this city. They note that the guerrillas have not 
received "any written communication" regarding the proposed 
amnesty announced last week by the government, which would cover 
rebel actions staged between 1 and 16 January. 
  In this regard, the rebels note that the "mentioned amnesty 
law" is "premature in the current dialogue process, because the 
political and social causes that gave rise to our movement still 
prevail." 

</TEXT>

