<H3> <TI>   Salinas Installs Commission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2001203294 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2001203294 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hour" newscast] </F>
  [Excerpts] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari has 
appointed Beatriz Paredes Rangel president of the National 
Commission for the Overall Development of and Social Justice for 
Indian Peoples [Comision Nacional de Desarrollo Integral y 
Justicia Social para los Pueblos Indigenas], which was created 
by Presidential Agreement on Wednesday [19 January] as published 
in the official gazette. At 2000 President Salinas held a 
30-minute meeting with Mrs. Paredes and representatives of 
several churches, indigenous community leaders, prominent 
intellectual figures, authors, actors, and other Mexican 
citizens to install the advisory commission for the National 
Commission for Overall Development and Social Justice for 
Indigenous Peoples. The meeting took place in the Vicente 
Guerrero Room at Los Pinos, the official presidential residence. 
The advisory commission held its first meeting at Los Pinos, 
which lasted two hours, prior to meeting with President Salinas. 
[passage omitted] 
  President Salinas is scheduled to meet with 42 
representatives of more than 200 indigenous groups this 
Thursday. The official list of members of the National 
Commission for Overall Development and Social Justice for 
Indigenous Peoples will be completed in the next few days. 

</TEXT>

