<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Robaina Continues African Tour </TI></H3>
<H4>   Travels to Namibia </H4>
<F P=102> FL1901140594 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1000 
GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL1901140594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina will travel 
to Namibia today. The Cuban foreign minister's official visit 
to Namibia will conclude a tour of several African nations. 
Robaina will arrive in Namibia from Zambia, where he met with 
Zambian President Frederick Chiluba. During the meeting with 
Robaina, President Chiluba thanked Cuba for helping Zambia in 
the health field. Chiluba also stressed that ties between Lusaka 
and Havana are very strong. Robaina delivered a message to 
Chiluba from President Fidel Castro and, on behalf of the people 
and government of Cuba, thanked the people of Zambia for their 
solidarity. 

</TEXT>

