<H3> <TI>   Vice Foreign Minister Ends Visit to Canary Islands </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2001141394 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2001141394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Vice Foreign Minister Isabel Allende has 
concluded a working visit to Las Palmas, Canary Islands, where 
she met with political and government officials. The vice 
foreign minister met with Manuel Hermozo, president of the 
government of the Canary Islands, and with Jesus Gomez, vice 
president of the Canary Islands council. The island authorities 
confirmed a coming visit to Cuba by representatives of the 
government of the Canary Islands to sign an agreement for the 
renovation of the building that will house the headquarters of 
the Cuban-Canary Islands Association. 
  Allende's working visit to Spain began on 11 January in 
Madrid where she met with high-ranking Spanish Foreign Ministry 
officials to analyze relations between the two countries and to 
prepare for Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina's scheduled visit 
to Spain. 

</TEXT>

