<H3> <TI>   Raul Castro Concludes Cienfuegos Work Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2001021094 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 0000 
GMT 20 Jan 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2001021094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On the last day of his work visit to Cienfuegos 
Province, Army General Raul Castro Ruz, minister of the FAR 
[Revolutionary Armed Forces], visited (El Jobero), the first 
community of materials-efficient housing finished in that 
province by Military Construction Enterprise No. 3 from Villa 
Clara. The residents of the community are officers and civilian 
workers who, by residing there along with their relatives, 
contribute to raising the combat readiness of their unit. 
  Castro, who is also second secretary of the Central 
Committee 
of the Communist Party of Cuba, asked about the living 
conditions of the residents of (El Jobero), who have, among 
other facilities, a Family Doctor Program physician and other 
services nearby. 
  Also, in Cumanayagua, the FAR minister visited the Barajagua 
People's Council, one of Cienfuegos' most outstanding; and, at 
the special troops regiment, heard a report from Colonel Jose 
Antonio Marrero on the unit's preparation and combat readiness. 
  Upon taking his leave, Raul reiterated that we can be proud 
of our four armies -- the Central, the Western, the Eastern, and 
the Youth Labor Army; of our Revolutionary Armed Forces; of our 
heroic people; and of our commander in chief, Fidel Castro. 

</TEXT>

