<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   President-Elect Reina Appoints New Ministers </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2001191494 San Pedro Sula LA PRENSA in Spanish 19 Jan 94 p 
4 </F>

<F P=103> PA2001191494 </F>
<F P=104>  San Pedro Sula LA PRENSA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Tegucigalpa -- President-elect Carlos Roberto Reina 
yesterday confirmed the appointment of three more ministers who 
will be ratified upon his return from the United States, where 
he is conducting an official visit. 
  Juan Ferrara, current president of the Honduran Council for 
Private Enterprise, COHEP, will be the new finance and public 
credit minister, while banker Delmer Urbizo Panting will occupy 
the post that Carlos Chain will vacate in the Economy and 
Commerce Ministry on 27 January. In addition, sociologist and 
economist Guillermo Molina Chocano will be the new planning, 
coordination, and budget minister. 
  Ferrara, Urbizo, Molina, and Hugo Noe Pine, Central Bank of 
Honduras president, accompanied President-elect Reina to 
Washington as members of the economic cabinet. 
  Reina said that the full cabinet will be announced after his 
meeting with former Liberal Party presidential hopefuls. 
  These three new ministers join those who were confirmed: 
Ernesto Paz Aguilar at the Foreign Affairs Ministry, Ramon 
Villeda Bermudez at the Natural Resources Ministry, and Enrique 
Samayoa at the Public Health and Social Aid Ministry. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

