<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Sources Claim Attack Leaves Capital Without Power </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2101154694 Paris AFP in Spanish 1511 GMT 21 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2101154694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Guatemala City, 21 Jan (AFP) -- A power outage, 
caused apparently by an attack or sabotage attempt, has left the 
Guatemalan capital city and a large part of the country without 
electricity, official sources reported today. 
  Electric company authorities who were contacted by AFP 
claimed not to know the cause of the outage, which occurred at 
0815 [1415 GMT], or when service will be restored. 
  Guatemala has experienced an escalation of attacks over the 
past 48 hours, with bomb explosions in the Congress and in four 
telecommunications towers in the western region of the country, 
which local media have attributed to leftist guerrillas. 

</TEXT>

