<F P=100> Guatemala </F>
<H3> <TI>   Attorney General Condemns Recent Terrorist Attacks </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2201040094 Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE in Spanish 21 Jan 
94 p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PA2201040094 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City PRENSA LIBRE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] In condemning the wave of terrorist attacks 
occurring just as the referendum is about to be held, Attorney 
General Jorge Mario Garcia Laguardia said yesterday that the use 
of explosives is not the solution to Guatemala's political 
crisis. 
  Garcia Laguardia called on the masterminds of the terrorist 
attacks to refrain from such practices and to seek other means 
of solving problems. He also indicated that actions such as 
these endanger the lives of innocent people who are not 
responsible for the problems. 
  The attorney general was referring specifically to the 
explosion in front of Channel 7 this past Tuesday, the one 
between 18th Street and 6th Avenue the day before yesterday, and 
the one in front of the National Congress building early 
yesterday morning. Garcia also stated that other explosive 
devices had been deactivated throughout the city. 
  Garcia Laguardia said that those who intend to destabilize 
the democratic system through terrorism and anarchy should 
reconsider because their attitude is not good for Guatemalans; 
on the contrary, it only endangers the lives of others. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

