<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sandinists Back Document Signed Jointly With UNO </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2301191694 Managua BARRICADA in Spanish 22 Jan 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> PA2301191694 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua BARRICADA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Statement issued by the Secretariat of the Sandinist </F>
National Liberation Front National Directorate in Managua on 21 
January 1994] 
  [Text] During its regular meeting on 21 January, the 
National Directorate of the Sandinist National Liberation Front 
[FSLN] analyzed the letter on reforms to the Constitution signed 
by 13 National Assembly deputies. 
  The National Directorate hereby ratifies its total backing 
for the Document on Agreements, a document that was signed on 29 
November by the Constitutional Commission of the National 
Opposition Union [UNO] and by the FSLN commission. The National 
Directorate also states its disposition to meet with the 
13-deputy commission integrated by Dr. Miriam Arguello, who 
heads it, and Adolfo Jarquin, Dr. Edmundo Castillo, and Zacarias 
Hernandez, to discuss the reforms to the Constitution issue. 
  During the session, the FSLN National Directorate condemned 
the assassination of Nicaraguan citizen Juan Pablo Cruz Laguna 
at the hands of members of the Honduran Armed Forces. The 
National Directorate demands of the Honduran Government that it 
clear the crime and punish the guilty persons; and of the 
Nicaraguan Government, the National Directorate demands that it 
carry out the necessary work so that the guilty parties are 
punished and Nicaraguan citizens in transit through Honduras are 
offered security. 
  The National Directorate expresses its condolences and 
solidarity to the relatives of Juan Pablo Cruz Laguna. 
  [Issued] Managua, 21 January 1994 
  Free Fatherland or death! 
  [Signed] Secretariat of the National Directorate, Sandinist 
National Liberation Front 

</TEXT>

