<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   MINA, Popular Alliance Endorse Carles Candidacy </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2301004794 Panama City EL SIGLO In Spanish 21 Jan 94 p 8 </F>
<F P=103> PA2301004794 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City EL SIGLO In Spanish 21 Jan 94 p 8 </F>



<TEXT>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Communique issued by the National Integration Movement, </F>
MINA, and Popular Alliance; place and date not given] 
  [Text] The Popular Alliance and MINA [National Integration 
Movement] political parties have been subject to what is 
obviously a discriminatory measure by the Electoral Tribunal 
magistrates. 
  The Electoral Tribunal magistrates' decision is intended to 
deprive our organizations of the right to participate in the 
upcoming elections and thus put us in a disadvantageous position 
compared to other political groups. 
  Being the active organizations we are and based on our legal 
status as political parties involved in their organization 
process, instead of refraining from action, we are issuing an 
appeal to all our supporters, urging them to double their 
efforts, defend our principles, and actively participate in the 
presidential campaign of Professor Ruben Carles and his slate, 
to which we offer our total support. We will thus support the 
Panamanian people's hope for a true change. 
  (signed) Dr. Arrigo Guardia 
  (signed) Professor Noris de Correa 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

