<F P=100> Venezuela </F>
<H3> <TI>   Rioting Continues; 5 Injured </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA1901221894 Paris AFP in Spanish 2122 GMT 19 Jan 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA1901221894 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] Caracas, 19 Jan (AFP) -- Reliable sources report 
that violent riots and looting continued to shake Venezuela 
today, leaving at least five people injured. 
  The eastern tourist resort of Puerto La Cruz has been 
enduring riots since last week. Today rioting spread into 
Caracas. There also were violent demonstrations near the 
Central University of Venezuela and two secondary schools. 
  The riots in Puerto La Cruz, where for the second day in a 
row businesses were looted, began because of a fare increase in 
public transportation. Yesterday, bus drivers refused to drive 
their routes because of the increase. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>
